      <p><a title="Tell us how we're doing" href="/feedback"><img src="/sites/default/files/uploads/images/general/feedback.png" alt="Tell us how we're doing" width="210" height="127" /></a></p>  
</section>      </aside>
    
          <aside role="complementary" class="large-3 l-sidebar-second columns sidebar" id="sub-2">
            <section class="block block-block block-block-16 block-even clearfix">

        <h3 class="block-title">News &amp; Events</h3>
    
      <h4><a href="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/locations-hours#holiday-closures" title="Holiday closures">Holiday closures</a></h4><p>All branches will be closed on Sunday, May 22 and Monday, May 23 for Victoria Day.</p><h4><a href="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/have-you-recently-received-your-canadian-citizenship" title="Cultural Access Pass">Cultural Access Pass</a></h4><p>Are you a new Canadian citizen? Get your Cultural Access Pass and visit more than 600 cultural attractions across Canada, all for free!</p><h4><a title="NewToBC.ca" href="http://newtobc.ca/">NewToBC</a></h4><p>NewToBC unites 10 public library systems in Metro Vancouver to help connect newcomers with programs and services in their community.</p><h4><a title="Metrotown transit notice" href="/news/metrotown-transit-notice">Metrotown transit notice</a></h4><p>The elevator at the Metrotown SkyTrain station is out of service until Winter 2017, due to station upgrades.</p>  
</section>  <section class="block block-views block-views-we-recommend-block-2 block-odd clearfix">

        <h3 class="block-title">We Recommend...</h3>
    
      <div class="view view-we-recommend view-id-we_recommend view-display-id-block_2 view-dom-id-d143874980fde41c0edb48e7d4125cd4">
        
  
  
      <div class="view-content">
        <div class="views-row views-row-1 views-row-odd views-row-first">
      
          <div><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/1132788002"><img src="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/sites/default/files/styles/we_recommend/public/uploads/materials/images/all-the-birds-in-the-sky.jpg?itok=fK9mS8q5" width="72" height="109" alt="All the Birds in the Sky, by Charlie Jane Anders" /></a></div>    
          <h4 class="term-link"><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/1132788002">All the Birds in the Sky</a></h4>    
  <div>        <em>Charlie Jane Anders</em>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-body">        <div class="field-content"><p>A good read for those who enjoyed <a title="station Eleven" href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/1080032002">Station Eleven</a> though a very different take on the collapse of human society. This collapse is driven not by disease but by our human need to continually strive for bigger and better. At the heart of the story are Patricia, who endures a lonely childhood and uncomfortable adolescence to become a practioner of magic, and Laurence, her only friend and confidant, who is a tech genius. The collision of the priorities of these two separate worlds defines their relationship and ultimately decides the fate of the world.</p></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-edit-node">        <span class="field-content"></span>  </div>  </div>
  <div class="views-row views-row-2 views-row-even views-row-last">
      
          <div><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/1118264002"><img src="http://www.bpl.bc.ca/sites/default/files/styles/we_recommend/public/uploads/materials/images/light-years.jpg?itok=aetGF5yQ" width="72" height="108" alt="Light Years, by Caroline Woodward" /></a></div>    
          <h4 class="term-link"><a href="https://burnaby.bibliocommons.com/item/show/1118264002">Light Years</a></h4>    
  <div>        <em>Caroline Woodward</em>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-body">        <div class="field-content"><p>In 2007, Caroline, a book rep travelling around Vancouver Island, and her husband Jeff were looking for a change. A chance meeting on a ferry leads them to explore lighthouse keeping. An up-beat and charming look at the unusual, sometimes difficult, and sometimes enviable life of the keepers – remote from what we tend to consider "civilization" but surrounded by wild beauty and the freedom to, for Caroline, pursue her writing, and for Jeff, his photography. There is also hard labour. Beginning with a 3:30 a.m. weather report, the days are filled with maintaining the light station buildings, sea sampling, radio communication, beach cleanup, wildlife encounters and everything in between. As for dangerous rescue missions or dramatic shipwrecks – that kind of excitement is rare. Caroline writes that "So far the only life I know I've saved is my own".</p></div>  </div>  
  <div class="views-field views-field-edit-node">        <span class="field-content"></span>  </div>  </div>
    </div>
  
  
  
      
